Please note that the current article has a section entitled "Scientific studies" (perhaps needing cleanup?). It links to a main article entitled  [[Research on meditation]], which has a subsection called "Brain waves during meditation".  So perhaps 32cllou should devote his/her available efforts to ensuring that that section is well done. 

In terms of mentioning scientific findings within this main article on meditation, I recall that our thinking has been that there's too much scientific research, and there are too many different points of view on it, to fit it all into this main article. Only highlights are possible - and I do see that "brain activation" is mentioned here as one of the findings about meditation. That could be expaned a bit, I'm sure, if there are secondary sources that can give a clear sense of what the nature (i.e., major and sustained findings) of those brain activation studies have been. But most if not all of the details and citations to single studies should be relegated to the other article on [[Research on meditation]]. Ideally, that article should be made high-quality, and this article's subsection can condense its most relevant key points. -- [[User:Presearch|Presearch]] ([[User talk:Presearch|talk]]) 19:27, 7 March 2012 (UTC)

